.TH PKGMAN-LIST 8 "PKGMAN-#VERSION# Manual"

.SH NAME
pkgman-list \- print list of available packages

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B pkgman list [-v|-vv] [--path] [--all] [--depsort] [--regex]
.BI [--filter= NAME ]

.SH DESCRIPTION
Print list of available packages.
.br
It looks in all directories specified in \fC/etc/pkgman.conf\fR.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-v
Show version in the listing.
.TP
.B \-vv
Show version and description in the listing.
.TP
.B \-\-path
Show package' source path in the listing.
.TP
.B \-\-all
List all packages, not only installed.
.TP
.B \-\-depsort
List the packages sorted by dependency.
.TP
.B \-\-regex
Interpret filter argument as a regular expression.
.TP
.BI \-\-filter= NAME
Filter listing packages by name. The filter option argument may be the
string, wildcard or regex.

